==English==

===Etymology===
From {{NL.}} '''[[camera obscura]]''', ''dark chamber'', because the first cameras used a [[pinhole]] and a dark room; from Latin '''camera''', ''[[chamber]]'' or ''[[bedchamber]]'', from Greek '''kamara''' ("vault".)

